text: Barakee National Park is a national park in the east of the Australian state of New South Wales, 257 km north of Sydney and about 110 km west of Port Macquarie. Steve Parish: Australian Touring Atlas. Steve Parish Publishing, Archerfield QLD 2007, ISBN 978-1-74193-232-4, S. 27 The national park is located on the north bank of the Nowendoc River. Barakee National Park. NSW Environment & Heritage Office The park has an area of 49.8km2 and became a national park on January 1 1999. == Web links == * Barakee National Park .
